  <title>Dynamic display compass</title>
  <purpose>
    <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:my="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003/myXSD/2006-02-10T23:25:53">This sample demonstrates drawing on the map in dynamic mode using an OpenGL application programming interface (API). A command is implemented that adds a compass object to the map, which rotates along together with the dynamic map. The following issues are covered in this sample: </div>
    <ul style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0px" type="disc" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:my="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003/myXSD/2006-02-10T23:25:53">
      <li>Wiring dynamic map events to listen to the Before or After DynamicDraw, which allows you to plug in your drawing to the map.</li>
      <li>Creation of OpenGL display lists.</li>
      <li>Mapping a bitmap into an OpenGL texture and binding the texture to an OpenGL geometry.</li>
      <li>Translating, scaling, and rotating OpenGL display lists. </li>
    </ul>
  </purpose>
